<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-450-044  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 450 044.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Software  July 1989 v6 n4 p20(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Faust: an integrated environment for parallel programming.andO;(contains a related article comparing Faust to other programmingenvironments) (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Guarna, Vincent A., Jr.; Gannon, Dennis; Jablonowski, David;Malony, Allen D.; Gaur, Yogesh.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Center for Supercomputing research and development at theUniversity of Illinois (Urbana-Champaign) is developing anintegrated parallel-programming environment, Faust, forlarge-scale scientific applications.andP;  The Faust toolset isspecifically designed to enable the workstation-based developmentof programs for parallel-processing machines.andP;  Other major designgoals include integration of new Faust tools with existingediting, compiling, and other tools without modification, andportability.andP;  Faust features an X-Windows interface; a ProjectManager, for management of programming 'object' components throughthe use of directed graphs and maintenance of a database ofcomponent functions; the Sigma tool for fine-tuning and optimizingparallel code; and several tools for performance analysis.andP;  Theenvironment is currently implemented on a UNIX-based Apolloworkstation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Research and DevelopmentProgramming LanguagesParallel ProcessingSystem DesignSpecificationsApplicationsProgram Development Tools.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   Faust organization. (chart)Comparing Faust. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>